    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-07-25T08:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-07-25T08:00:00-05:00" n="365"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d365">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">124.842/142: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Italy</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Kirk</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rome</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-07-25T14:00:00+01:00"
                            >July 25, 1936—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received July 25—9:45 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>290. Department’s 93, July 24, 4 p.m. I have just called at the Foreign Office
                    and requested a clarification of Graziani’s decree of July 21. I was informed
                    that an inquiry would be immediately addressed to the Ministry of Colonies and
                    that a reply might be expected within 2 or 3 days.</p>
                <p>The British Embassy here has been notified of this decree but as yet has received
                    no instructions from London.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kirk</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
